eld%20for%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolling%20will%20be%20held%20in%20seven%20phases%20starting%20April%2019.%20Phase%201%20voting%20on%20April%2019%2C%C2%A0%20Phase%202%20on%20April%2026%2C%20Phase%203%20on%20May%207%2C%20Phase%204%20on%20May%2013%2C%20Phase%205%20on%20May%2020%2C%20Phase%206%20on%20May%2025%20and%20Phase%207%20on%20June%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20When%20will%20counting%20of%20votes%20be%20held%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20will%20be%20announced%20on%20June%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20How%20many%20people%20will%20vote%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20total%20of%2096.8%20crore%20people%20are%20eligible%20to%20vote%20in%20the%20upcoming%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%20This%20includes%201.8%20crore%20Indians%20who%20recently%20turned%2018%20and%20will%20be%20eligible%20to%20cast%20their%20vote%20for%20the%20first-time%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20Who%20is%20eligible%20to%20be%20registered%20as%20a%20voter%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20To%20be%20eligible%20for%20voter%20registration%2C%20one%20must%20be%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20at%20least%2018%20years%20of%20age%2C%20and%20an%20ordinary%20resident%20of%20the%20area%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20How%20can%20one%20get%20registered%2Fenrolled%20in%20the%20electoral%20roll%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20To%20get%20registered%2C%20one%20needs%20to%20file%20an%20application%20in%20the%20prescribed%20Form%206%20(Form%206A%20for%20overseas%20Indians)%20before%20the%20Electoral%20Registration%20Officer%20(ERO)%2FAssistant%20Electoral%20Registration%20Officer%20(AERO)%20of%20the%20constituency%20where%20the%20applicant%20resides.%20The%20application%20can%20be%20submitted%20in%20person%2C%20by%20post%2C%20or%20online%20through%20various%20portals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20How%20many%20seats%20are%20going%20to%20polls%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20A%20total%20of%20543%20Parliamentary%20constituencies%20will%20go%20to%20polls%20in%20the%20upcoming%20general%20election.%20Additionally%2C%20four%20states%E2%80%94Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Sikkim%E2%80%94will%20vote%20in%20Assembly%20elections%20alongside%20the%20national%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20What%20if%20I%20can't%20find%20my%20name%20in%20the%20electoral%20rolls%2C%20who%20do%20I%20go%20to%20for%20help%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20If%20your%20name%20is%20missing%20from%20the%20electoral%20rolls%2C%20you%20can%20contact%20the%20nearest%20Election%20Commission%20office%20or%20visit%20the%20National%20Voters'%20Services%20Portal%20at%20www.nvsp.in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20What%20if%20I%20don't%20have%20an%20election%20card%3F%20How%20do%20I%20register%3F%20Can%20I%20register%20online%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20Even%20without%20an%20election%20ID%20card%2C%20you%20can%20still%20vote%20using%20most%20government-issued%20photo%20identity%20documents.%20Online%20registration%20is%20possible%20through%20various%20portals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20What%20is%20NOTA%20and%20when%20was%20it%20introduced%3F%20Which%20state%20has%20had%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20NOTA%20votes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20NOTA%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BNone%20Of%20The%20Above%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20voting%20option%20on%20Electronic%20Voting%20Machines%20(EVMs)%20introduced%20in%20October%202013%20following%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20order.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20has%20recorded%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20NOTA%20votes%20in%20past%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQ%3A%20What%20are%20bellwether%20seats%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%3A%20Bellwether%20seats%20are%20those%20that%20historically%20vote%20for%20the%20eventual%20winner