rts%20using%20different%20formats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20several%20companies%20are%20answerable%20to%20shareholders%2C%20it%20becomes%20important%20to%20note%20how%20this%20information%2C%20of%20money%20to%20some%20political%20parties%2C%20was%20conveyed%20publicly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fmany-firms-report-electoral-%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20finds%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20data%20has%20been%20shown%20under%20%E2%80%9Cmiscellaneous%20expenses%20and%20donations%E2%80%9D%20with%20a%20note%20explaining%20the%20amount%20spent%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20writes%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20reading%20of%20the%20reports%20suggests%20that%20there%20is%20no%20standard%20practice%20for%20reporting%20political%20contributions%20and%20it%20is%20left%20to%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20discretion%20to%20report%20them%20as%20they%20find%20fit.%20Many%20companies%20have%20clubbed%20all%20donations%20without%20giving%20a%20breakup%2C%20while%20a%20lot%20of%20large%20purchasers%20have%20not%20mentioned%20bonds%20in%20their%20annual%20reports%20at%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4ZNgU%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20companies%20recorded%20electoral%20bond%20transactions%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22704%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analysis%20notes%20that%20as%20per%20annual%20report%20filings%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmining%20and%20metal%20major%20Vedanta%20spent%20the%20most%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20FY23%2C%20followed%20by%20Bharti%20Airtel%20and%20Jindal%20Steel%20%26amp%3B%20Power.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20large%20companies%20that%20reported%20purchases%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20or%20political%20contributions%20in%20FY23%20include%20Mahindra%20%26amp%3B%20Mahindra%20(Rs%2025%20crore)%2C%20Cipla%20(Rs%2024.2%20crore)%2C%20Torrent%20Power%20(Rs%2023%20crore)%2C%20Aurobindo%20Pharma%20(Rs%2021.5%20crore)%2C%20Maruti%20Suzuki%20(Rs%2020%20crore)%20and%20Hero%20MotoCorp%20(Rs%2020%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20Labs%20while%20it%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2080%20crore%20between%202019%20and%202024%2C%20does%20not%20mention%20it%20in%20the%20annual%20report.%20The%20same%20is%20true%20for%20Divi%E2%80%99s%20Laboratories%2C%20PCBL%2C%20and%20Torrent%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20political%20funding%20in%20their%20annual%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20analysis%20finds%20that%20many%20large%20political%20contributors%20%E2%80%9Csuch%20as%20Hindalco%20Industries%2C%20DLF%2C%20UPL%2C%20and%20Zydus%20Lifesciences%20have%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20through%20their%20unlisted%20subsidiaries.%E2%80%9D%20This%20means%20they%20have%20felt%20no%20need%20to%20report%20it%20in%20the%20annual%20reports%20of%20the%20parent%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fifb-agro-industries-bengal-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Ereported%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20earlier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20company%20the%20West%20Bengal-based%20IFB%20Agro%20openly%20said%20last%20month%20that%C2%A0%20it%20had%20paid%20Rs%2040%20crore%20in%20Electoral%20Bonds%20this%20financial%20year%2C%20three%20times%20its%20profits%20after%20tax.%20The%20company%20had%20created%20a%20stir%20in%202022%20by%20declaring%20it%20will%20be%20donating%20electoral%20bonds.%20In%20a%20recording%20of%20IFB%20Agro%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifbagro.in%2Fassets%2Fimages%2Finvestor_relations%2FIFB%2520Agro%2520Industries%2520Limited.mp4%5C%22%3Eannual%20general%20meeting%20of%20FY%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20on%20July%2031%2C%202023%2C%20a%20shareholder%20is%20heard%20mentioning%20electoral%20bond%20payments%20over%20its%20spirits%20b