S)%20gave%20a%20call%20to%20its%20party%20cadres%20to%20hold%20demonstrations%20across%20Telangana%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20minister%20and%20BRS%20leader%2C%20T.%20Harish%20Rao%2C%20described%20Kavitha%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20in%20the%20Delhi%20liquor%20policy%20case%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconspiracy%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20Congress%20to%20gain%20political%20mileage%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20He%20said%20both%20parties%20are%20trying%20hard%20to%20demoralise%20BRS%20chief%20K.%20Chandrasekhar%20Rao%20and%20party%20workers%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20all%20set%20to%20announce%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cundemocratic%2C%20illegal%2C%20and%20unethical%E2%80%9D%2C%20Harish%20Rao%20said%20the%20arrest%20was%20carried%20out%20on%20Friday%20evening%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20launching%20legal%20proceedings%2C%20as%20Saturday%20and%20Sunday%20are%20court%20holidays.%20He%20recalled%20that%20BJP%20leaders%20and%20Union%20ministers%20had%20been%20issuing%20threatening%20statements%20about%20Kavitha%E2%80%99s%20impending%20arrest%20for%20the%20past%20one-and-a-half%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20questioned%20the%20arrest%20stating%20that%20it%20was%20done%20merely%20three%20days%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20set%20to%20hear%20a%20bunch%20of%20petitions%20filed%20by%20Kavitha%2C%20Nalini%20Chidambaram%2C%20and%20a%20relative%20of%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20challenging%20the%20questioning%20of%20women%20at%20the%20offices%20of%20investigating%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Kavitha%20left%20for%20the%20airport%20in%20the%20car%20of%20ED%2C%20as%20she%20was%20flown%20to%20Delhi%20by%20officials.%20She%20flashed%20a%20victory%20sign%20as%20she%20got%20into%20the%20car%20and%20her%20brother%2C%20K.T.%20Rama%20Rao%2C%20consoled%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERama%20Rao%20too%20left%20for%20Delhi%20separately%2C%20immediately%20after%20Kavitha%20was%20taken%20away.%20He%20is%20said%20to%20be%20camping%20in%20Delhi%20to%20arrange%20legal%20aid%20for%20his%20sister%20with%20senior%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20police%20resorted%20to%20a%20mild%20lathi%20charge%20when%20BRS%20party%20workers%20and%20supporters%20tried%20to%20construct%20the%20convoy%20of%20ED.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20ED%20lodged%20a%20police%20complaint%20against%20Rama%20Rao%20at%20Banjara%20Hills%20police%20station%20for%20allegedly%20obstructing%20ED%20officials%20from%20carrying%20out%20their%20work%2C%20and%20on%20the%20accusation%20that%20he%20forced%20his%20way%20into%20Kavitha%E2%80%99s%20house%20where%20searches%20were%20being%20conducted.%20ED%20official%20Bhanu%20Priya%20Meena%20in%20her%20complaint%20said%20that%20Rama%20Rao%20had%20threatened%20the%20officials%2C%20who%20were%20discharging%20their%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Union%20minister%20and%20BJP%20state%20president%20G.%20Kishan%20Reddy%20hurriedly%20convened%20a%20teleconference%20with%20party%20leaders%20asking%20them%20not%20to%20speak%20about%20the%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20alliance%20partner%20of%20BRS%2C%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20arrest%20was%20part%20of%20blackmail%20tactics%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20to%20check%20the%20secular%20agenda%20of%20the%20two%20parties%2C%20both%20of%20which%20were%20opposed%20to%20BJP%20and%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710575958000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16130523%2FGIuDp2ga0AAJNq-.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkavithas-arrest-brs-gives-call-for-statewide-protests-dubs-it-as-conspiracy-of-bjp%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20officials%20of%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20also%20filed%20a%20police%20complaint%20against%20Kavitha's%20brother%20and%20former%20minister%20K.T.%20Rama%20Rao%20alleging%20that%20he%20obstructed%20them%20from%20carrying%20out%20their%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkavithas-arrest-brs-gives-call-for-statewide-protests-dubs-it-as-conspiracy-of-bjp%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%20Five%20Political%20Parties%20Saw%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Fortunes%20Turning%20With%20Election%20Wins%20and%20Losses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16131951%2Fimage-1970.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20top%20five%20political%20parties%20that%20encashed%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2011%2C082%20crore%20from%20private%20companies%20from%20April%202019%20to%20January%202024%2C%20had%20their%20fate%20decided%20by%20perceptions%20and%20outcomes%20in%20elections%2C%20data%20uploaded%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20on%20its%20website%20on%20March%2014%20reveals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20five%20political%20parties%20include%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20that%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%206%2C060.5%20crore%2C%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%201%2C609.5%20crore%2C%20the%20Congress%20at%20the%20third%20spot%20received%20Rs%201%2C421.8%20crores%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20encashed%20Rs%201%2C214.7%20crore%2C%20and%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20received%20Rs%20775.5%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20published%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20includes%20information%20about%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C769%20crore%20from%20April%2012%2C%202019%20to%20January%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20its%20order%20immediately%20nixing%20electoral%20bonds%20on%20February%2015%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20also%20a%20legitimate%20possibility%20that%20financial%20contributions%20to%20a%20political%20party%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fquid-pro-quo-how-revealing-electoral-bonds-will-clear-questions-of-len-den%5C%22%3Equid%20pro%20quo%20arrangemen%3C%2Fa%3Et%20because%20of%20the%20close%20nexus%20between%20money%20and%20politics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20in%20top%20spot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20is%20the%20largest%20recipient%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%206%2C060.5%20crore%20as%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20it%20encashed%20the%20majority%20before%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20followed%20by%20the%202021%20and%202023%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20redeemed%20Rs%201%2C771.57%20crore%20worth%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20April%20and%20May%202019%2C%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20The%202019%20general%20election%20in%20India%20earned%20the%20dubious%20highlight%20of%20being%20the%20most%20expensive%20election%20in%20the%20world%2C%20more%20expensive%20than%20the%20one%20in%20the%20US%20in%202016.%20A%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-06-03%2Findia-s-bitterly-fought-poll-becomes-the-world-s-most-expensive%5C%22%3Ecited%20by%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20%248.7%20billion%20were%20spent%20in%20that%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20in%20July%202019%2C%20after%20the%20polls%2C%20it%20encashed%20bonds%20only%20worth%20Rs%2015%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20January%20and%20April%202021%2C%20with%20key%20state%20assembly%20elections%20due%20in%20four%20states%20and%20one%20Union%20Territory%2C%20including%20West%20Bengal%20(where%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20looking%20to%20wrest%20power%20from%20the%20TMC)%2C%20Assam%20(that%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20key%20stronghold%20in%20the%20northeast%20since%202016)%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Kerala%20(southern%20states%20where%20the%20BJP%20is%20yet%20to%20make%20electoral%20inroads)%20and%20Puducherry%2C%20it%20redeemed%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20292%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20between%20July%20and%20October%202021%20%E2%80%93%20when%20elections%20were%20over%20%E2%80%93%20the%20party%20only%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2080%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%20when%20assembly%20elections%20were%20due%20in%20key%20Hindi%20heartland%20states%20(two%20of%20which%20were%20Congress-ruled)%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%20along%20with%20Telangana%20and%20Mizoram%2C%20the%20BJP%20encashed%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%201%2C149%20crore%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20polls%20between%20July%20and%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20the%20party%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20527%20crore%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%20%E2%80%93%20between%20January%20and%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVrySE%2F2%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22BJP's%20electoral%20bond%20fortunes%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETMC%3A%20a%20surprise%20%232%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20a%20regional%20party%2C%20has%20surprisingly%20surpassed%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20main%20national%20opposition%20party%2C%20by%20encashing%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%201%2C609.5%20crore%20between%20April%202019%20and%20January%202024.%20This%20is%20considered%20significant%20for%20a%20party%20ruling%20just%20one%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20shows%20that%20the%20TMC%20got%20more%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20after%20its%20resounding%20victory%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%2C%20where%20it%20secured%20a%20third%20term%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20April%202019%20and%20April%202021%2C%20the%20TMC%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20196%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20it%20was%20after%20the%20assembly%20elections%20(results%20were%20declared%20on%20May%202%2C%202021)%20that%20the%20party%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20249%20crore%20between%20July%20and%20October%202021%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20the%20party%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20468%20crore%20in%202022%2C%20and%20Rs%20562%20crore%20in%202023%2C%20and%20Rs%20130%20crore%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FMSg3p%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Electoral%20Bonds%3A%20Fund%20flow%20for%20TMC%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECongress%20encashed%20more%20after%20state%20wins%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20TMC%2C%20which%20benefitted%20from%20its%20victory%20in%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%2C%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20Congress%20which%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%201%2C421.8%20crore%20also%20benefited%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20more%20after%20its%20victories%20and%20saw%20its%20fortunes%20dwindling%20after%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grand%20old%20party%20redeemed%20Rs%20168%20crore%20between%20April%20and%20May%202019%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20last%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20Donations%20dropped%20in%20the%20subsequent%20months%20after%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20landslide%20victory.%20Congress%20ended%20up%20redeeming%20just%20Rs%201.7%20crore%20in%20October%202019%2C%20and%20Rs%209%20crore%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%202021%2C%20its%20fortunes%20related%20to%20bonds%20improved%2C%20with%20data%20showing%20the%20party%20redeemed%20Rs%2065%20crore%20between%20January%20and%20April%20that%20year%20and%20then%20Rs%2058%20crore%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20January%20and%20April%202022%2C%20when%20elections%20were%20due%20in%20Punjab%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Manipur%2C%20and%20Goa%2C%20the%20party%20redeemed%20Rs%20127%20crore%20and%20subsequently%20went%20down%20to%20Rs%2037%20crore%20in%20October%20that%20year%20after%20losses%20in%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%2C%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20victory%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20in%20December%20that%20year%20turned%20its%20fortunes%20in%20getting%20donations%20via%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20lost%20the%20elections%20in%20the%20BJP%20bastion%20Gujarat%2C%20its%20victory%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20assembly%20elections%20(results%20were%20declared%20on%20December%208%2C%202022)%20perhaps%20helped%20the%20party%20secure%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20209%20crore%20between%20December%2013%2C%202022%20and%20April%2020%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20period%2C%20it%20received%20Rs%20190%20crore%20in%20April%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20ahead%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20elections%20where%20it%20recorded%20a%20resounding%20victory%2C%20after%20a%20large-scale%20disenchantment%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkarnataka-election-results-congress-victory%5C%22%3Ethe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20B.S.%20Bommai%20government%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20also%20made%20huge%20gains%20in%20the%20form%20of%20electoral%20bond%20donations%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202023%20assembly%20elections%2C%20where%20it%20was%20looking%20to%20retain%20power%20in%20two%20states%20(Chhattisgarh%20and%20Rajasthan)%20and%20dislodge%20the%20four-term%20BJP%20government%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20dislodge%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20November%2C%20the%20party%20encashed%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20401%20crore%20in%20October%20and%20Rs%20179%20crore%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20its%20defeat%20in%20the%20four%20of%20the%20five%20states%20(it%20only%20won%20Telangana)%2C%20the%20party%20encashed%20just%20Rs%2035%20crore%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYfmeK%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Funding%20figures%20for%20Congress%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBRS%20bond%20squeeze%20after%20loss%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20shows%20that%20the%20BRS%2C%20too%2C%20suffered%20losses%20in%20terms%20of%20donations%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20after%20its%20loss%20in%20the%202023%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Telangana%20which%20saw%20the%20party%20being%20routed%20after%20two%20terms%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BRS%20encashed%20Rs%2037%20crore%20between%20April%20and%20May%202019%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20data%20shows%20its%20fortunes%20seeing%20a%20huge%20jump%20after%20it%20redeemed%20Rs%20153%20crore%20in%20October%202021%2C%20rising%20further%20to%20being%20able%20to%20redeem%20Rs%20410%20crore%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20then%20encashed%20Rs%20118%20crore%20worth%20of%20bonds%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20party%20encashed%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2096%20crore%20between%20January%20and%20April%2C%20rising%20to%20Rs%20318%20crore%20in%20July.%20Ahead%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%2C%20where%20the%20Congress%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fa-resurgent-congress-in-telangana-and-the-challenges-for-brs-and-bjp%5C%22%3Egaining%20momentum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20BRS%20encashed%20Rs%2072%20crore%20in%20October%20and%20Rs%2013%20crore%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20its%20drubbing%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20(results%20for%20which%20were%20declared%20on%20December%203)%2C%20the%20party%20did%20not%20encash%20any%20further%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FaxP8u%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22BRS's%20windfall%20from%20electoral%20bonds%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJD%20received%20high%20amounts%20during%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJD%2C%20which%20is%20in%20power%20in%20Odisha%2C%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20775.5%20crore%2C%20according%20to%20data%20showing%20bonds%20it%20encashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20months%20after%20the%20party%20returned%20to%20power%20in%20the%20state%2C%20it%20encashed%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2010%20crore%20in%20July%2C%20followed%20by%20Rs%2010%20crore%20in%20January%202020%2C%20and%20Rs%2067%20crore%20in%20October%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20second%20wave%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20BJD%20encashed%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20116%20crore%20in%20April%202021%20and%20subsequently%20Rs%20125%20crore%20in%20October%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20it%20encashed%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20195%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20year%20ahead%20of%20elections%2C%20where%20the%20BJD%20is%20seeking%20a%20sixth%20consecutive%20term%20in%20power%2C%20the%20party%20has%20encashed%20Rs%20252%20crore%20between%20February%20and%20November%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20published%20on%20the%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20website%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fin-sbis-released-data-electoral-bonds-redeemed-amount-to-more-than-those-bought%5C%22%3Ewas%20released%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-case-sc-dismisses-sbis-plea-for-extension-says-disclose-information-by-march-12%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20furnish%20all%20details%20of%20those%20who%20had%20purchased%20and%20those%20who%20had%20encashed%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20since%202019.%20It%20had%20also%20asked%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20publish%20the%20data%20on%20its%20website%20by%20March%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20uploaded%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20a%20day%20before%20its%20Supreme%20Court-ordered%20deadline%20%E2%80%93%20includes%20two%20documents%3A%20a%20date-wise%20list%20of%20purchases%20by%20companies%20and%20a%20date-wise%20list%20of%20deposits%20by%20political%20parties%20that%20have%20encashed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20(March%2015)%20issued%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-issues-notice-to-sbi-for-not-releasing-unique-numbers-linked-to-electoral-bonds-bought-redeemed%5C%22%3Enotice%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20SBI%20for%20not%20releasing%20the%20bond%20numbers%20in%20the%20electoral%20bond%20data%20submitted%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20which%20it%20had%20made%20public%20on%20Thursday.%20Without%20the%20bond%20numbers%20being%20made%20available%20in%20either%20list%2C%20it%20was%20not%20possible%20to%20cross-verify%20which%20company%20or%20individual%20was%20donating%20to%20which%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710575481000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F16131951%2Fimage-1970.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftop-five-political-parties-saw-electoral-bonds-fortunes-turning-with-election-wins-and-losses%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20encashed%20majority%20of%20its%20bonds%2C%20Rs%201%2C771.57%20crore%2C%20before%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20The%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20receipts%20increased%20after%20its%202021%20election%20win.%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20bond-related%20fortunes%20rose%20after%20its%20win%20in%20Himachal%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20then%20dropped%20after%20the%202023%20losses%20as%20did%20the%20BRS%E2%80%99s%2C%20which%20dropped%20after%20its%202023%20shock%20assembly%20loss.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftop-five-political-parties-saw-electoral-bonds-fortunes-turning-with-election-wins-and-losses%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mice%20have%20overrun%20a%20remote%20island%20and%20are%20feasting%20on%20seabirds%20-%20now%20they%20face%20extermination%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710574320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-climate-change-mice-island_6491822.jpg%3F20240316080041%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmice-have-overrun-a-remote-island-and-are-feasting-on-seabirds-now-they-face-extermination-13095718%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20million%20out%20of%20control%20mice%20that%20are%20feasting%20on%20seabirds%20and%20causing%20havoc%20on%20a%20remote%20island%20are%20to%20be%20exterminated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmice-have-overrun-a-remote-island-and-are-feasting-on-seabirds-now-they-face-extermination-13095718%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmice-have-overrun-a-remote-island-and-are-feasting-on-seabirds-now-they-face-extermination-13095718%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmice-have-overrun-a-remote-island-and-are-feasting-on-seabirds-now-they-face-extermination-13095718%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20Admiral%20Ramdas%20And%20How%20India%20Was%20Different%20In%201984%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15144956%2FGIsGrdcW0AAoSLg.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20passing%20of%20Admiral%20Laxminarayan%20Ramdas%20evokes%20memories%20from%201984%20of%20a%20different%20India.%20Paradoxically%2C%20the%20only%20part%20he%20played%20in%20the%20events%20which%20evoked%20my%20recollections%20was%20possibly%20a%20conscious%20decision%20to%20look%20past%20what%20his%20other%20half%20and%20her%20associates%20were%20engaged%20in.%20That%20was%20the%20era%20when%20those%20in%20the%20regime%20were%20more%20sure-footed%20and%20did%20not%20shout%20%E2%80%98treason%E2%80%99%20at%20every%20step%20to%20consolidate%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20exactly%20four%20decades%20ago%2C%20had%20dawned%20in%20India%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Jarnail%20Singh%20Bhindranwale%20being%20openly%20revered%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Esant%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20saint%20by%20large%20sections%20in%20Punjab.%20Using%20this%20image%2C%20he%20had%20entered%20the%20Akal%20Takht%2C%20the%20highest%20temporal%20seat%20of%20the%20Sikhs%2C%20and%20fortified%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20priest%20of%20the%20Takht%20protested%20but%20was%20ignored%20and%20both%20the%20Shiromani%20Gurudwara%20Prabandhak%20Committee%20and%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20chose%20silence%20as%20the%20safest%20path.%20He%20had%20claimed%20earlier%20that%20the%20Sikhs%20never%20demanded%20a%20separate%20state%20of%20Khalistan%20but%20if%20the%20government%20granted%20them%20the%20wish%2C%20they%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20secede.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20posture%20became%20less%20nuanced%20after%20moving%20into%20the%20Akal%20Takht%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20for%20the%20government%20to%20make%20up%20its%20mind%20whether%20it%20wishes%20to%20remain%20with%20us%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bhindranwale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20doubt%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20lost%20her%20hold%20over%20the%20fundamentalists%20and%20the%20moderates%20had%20retreated%20far%20into%20the%20background.%20Eventually%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20made%20up%20her%20mind%20and%20began%20firming%20up%20plans%20for%20launching%20Operation%20Blue%20Star.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it%20was%20the%20gruesome%20assassination%20of%20Romesh%20Chandra%2C%20the%20editor%20of%20the%20Hind%20Samachar%20group%20%E2%80%94%20his%20father%20Lala%20Jagat%20Narain%20was%20also%20murdered%20by%20Sikh%20terrorists%20%E2%80%94%20in%20May%201984%2C%20which%20forced%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20seize%20control%20of%20the%20Golden%20Temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamchandra%20Guha%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20After%20Gandhi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20Operation%20Blue%20Star%20%E2%80%9Cleft%20a%20collective%20wound%20in%20the%20psyche%20of%20the%20Sikhs%2C%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20suspicion%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20shared%20grief%20erupted%20on%20October%2031%20in%20the%20action%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20constables%2C%20Beant%20Singh%20and%20Satwant%20Singh%20and%20the%20rest%20is%20well-known%2C%20including%20the%20gory%20carnage%20that%20followed%20which%20left%20thousands%20dead%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Kanpur%2C%20Bokaro%20and%20even%20distant%20cities%20like%20Indore%20and%20Coimbatore%2C%20which%20witnessed%20uncalled%20for%20violence%20against%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20retributive%20assassination%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20round%20of%20vengeful%20killings%20on%20a%20mass%20scale%2C%20first%20in%20the%20Indian%20capital%2C%20and%20later%20in%20other%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20was%20solely%20engrossed%20in%20managing%20the%20biggest%20funeral%20in%20several%20decades%2C%20this%20one%20made%20more%20poignant%20due%20to%20the%20circumstances%20that%20led%20to%20it.%20Delhi%20was%20burning%20much%20before%20her%20pyre%20was%20lit.%20Whichever%20direction%20one%20turned%20to%2C%20there%20was%20smoke%20billowing.%20All%20stories%20that%20arrived%20by%20word%20of%20mouth%20and%20courtesy%20brave%20young%20reporters%20of%20that%20time%2C%20spoke%20of%20dead%20bodies%20either%20in%20heaps%20or%20in%20scatters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20television%20screen%20of%20the%20only%20state%20channel%20available%20then%2C%20was%20fixated%20on%20the%20face%20of%20the%20deceased%20leader%20and%20on%20dignitaries%20who%20arrived%20to%20pay%20homage.%20Rioters%2C%20lynch%20brigades%2C%20and%20arsonists%20roamed%20those%20streets%20where%20the%20police%20should%20have%20been%20patrolling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterventions%20from%20the%20civil%20society%20usually%20take%20the%20courage%20of%20only%20a%20handful.%20Initially%2C%20just%20a%20small%20group%20assembled%20outside%20what%20was%20then%2C%20and%20still%20so%2C%20the%20little%20known%20Lajpat%20Bhawan%2C%20a%20property%20of%20the%20Servants%20of%20the%20People%20Society%2C%20established%20by%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%20in%20his%20Lahore%20home%20in%201921%20and%20later%20shifted%20to%20Delhi%20after%20partition.%20This%20was%20in%20addition%20to%20%E2%80%98peace%E2%80%99%20(and%20patrolling)%20committees%20in%20middle-class%20colonies%20across%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20walked%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20smoke%20that%20initially%20appeared%20to%20be%20across%20the%20Ring%20Road%20and%20beyond%20the%20Moolchand%20Hospital.%20Later%2C%20the%20smoke%20took%20them%20towards%20Bhogal%20and%20on%20the%20way%20they%20came%20across%20a%20mob%20breathing%20fire%20and%20ranting%20against%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobs%20are%20notoriously%20also%20weak-kneed%20and%20run%20short%20at%20the%20slightest%20bit%20of%20challenge.%20What%20made%20this%20group%20conspicuous%2C%20doing%20little%20but%20walking%2C%20reasoning%20and%20imploring%20with%20folded%20hands%2C%20was%20that%20it%20also%20included%20a%20man%20in%20saffron.%20In%20the%20India%20of%20that%20time%2C%20robes%20of%20this%20colour%20did%20not%20herald%20a%20zealot%20donning%20it.%20Instead%20it%20was%20the%20colour%20of%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwami%20Agnivesh%2C%20was%20not%20a%20guru%2C%20but%20an%20interventionist%20disillusioned%20with%20politics%20and%20much%20before%20such%20phrases%20caught%20on%2C%20was%20mainly%20a%20champion%20of%20marginal%20causes%3A%20rescuing%20child%20labour%20being%20one%20of%20those.%20After%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20which%20the%20group%20successfully%20sent%20back%20several%20marauding%20gangs%20with%20little%20but%20their%20persuasion%2C%20they%20assembled%20at%20the%20starting%20point%2C%20but%20this%20time%20inside%20the%20premises%20of%20this%20very%20Gandhian%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fex-naval-chief-admiral-laxminarayan-ramdas-passes-away-at-95%5C%22%3EAdmiral%20Ramdas%2C%20Former%20Navy%20Chief%20Who%20Fought%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Rights%2C%20Passes%20Away%20at%2090%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20any%20formal%20call%20being%20taken%2C%20this%20became%20the%20daily%20grind%20and%20as%20the%20group%20swelled%2C%20they%20travelled%20to%20far-flung%20areas%20from%20where%20%E2%80%98bad%E2%80%99%20or%20even%20%E2%80%98worse%E2%80%99%20news%20emanated.%20They%20drove%20their%20own%20cars%2C%20packing%20into%20the%20Fiats%2C%20Ambassadors%2C%20Standards%20and%20the%20odd%20Marutis.%20They%20went%20to%20distant%20localities%20and%20when%20a%20day%20or%20two%20later%2C%20they%20returned%20in%20the%20evening%20after%20seeing%20the%20grotesque%20scenes%20in%20Trilokpuri%2C%20all%20of%20them%20knew%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20shift%20gears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpontaneity%20was%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20effort%20and%20soon%20hundreds%20were%20assembling%20every%20morning%20at%20Lajpat%20Nagar.%20The%20Gandhian%20managers%20of%20the%20premises%2C%20threw%20open%20every%20large%20vacant%20hall%20or%20room%20to%20store%20items%20that%20could%20be%20distributed%20as%20relief%20%E2%80%93%20cereals%2C%20pulses%2C%20cooking%20oil%2C%20utensils.%20Others%20came%20with%20clothes%2C%20warm%2C%20just%20enough%20to%20shield%20modesty%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20turbans%20that%20had%20been%20pulled%20and%20set%20to%20fire%20or%20trampled%20upon%2C%20by%20the%20murderous%20hordes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20boss%20giving%20directions.%20Everyone%20took%20their%20own%20decisions%20with%20minor%20consultations%20to%20avoid%20duplication.%20For%20many%20in%20the%20city%2C%20especially%20in%20Lajpat%20Nagar%20%E2%80%94%20originally%20allotted%20to%20refugee%20families%20from%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%94%20this%20was%20partition%20once%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20young%20aspiring%20journalist%2Fresearcher%2Fdo-not-know-what%2C%20I%20too%20got%20involved%2C%20drawn%20by%20a%20doyen%20of%20the%20civil%20society.%20A%20morning%20meeting%20where%20%E2%80%98work%E2%80%99%20was%20sought%20and%20%E2%80%98allotted%E2%80%99%20was%20followed%20by%20different%20groups%20following%20different%20tasks.%20Some%20fanned%20out%20to%20gurudwaras%20across%20the%20city%20where%20hundreds%20of%20displaced%20and%20targeted%20families%20took%20refuge%20from%20the%20killers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20focused%20on%20providing%20food%20and%20distributing%20clothes%20to%20provide%20relief%20from%20the%20onset%20of%20winter%2C%20while%20others%20gathered%20information.%20There%20was%20much%20of%20that%20needed%3A%20how%20many%20had%20not%20survived%20the%20onslaught%2C%20which%20localities%20were%20worst%20hit%20and%20above%20all%2C%20who%20were%20the%20marauders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20came%20up%20with%20a%20name%20that%20stuck%3A%20Nagrik%20Ekta%20Manch.%20The%20word%20was%20passed%20around.%20Obviously%20well-heeled%20ones%20too%20trooped%20in%2C%20and%20said%20that%20they%20were%20leaving%20behind%20a%20car%20with%20the%20driver%20waiting%20for%20directions%20and%20the%20tank%20topped%20up.%20Known%20faces%20abounded%2C%20a%20writer%2C%20an%20artist%2C%20a%20Doordarshan%20anchor%2C%20a%20big%20industrialist%2C%20university%20professors%2C%20environmentalists%2C%20a%20retired%20army%20general%20and%20serving%20government%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20a%20noted%20historian%20of%20today%2C%20then%20an%20aspiring%20one%2C%20I%20led%20a%20team%20every%20day%20to%20a%20resettlement%20colony%20on%20the%20western%20fringe%20of%20the%20metropolis%20%E2%80%93%20some%20pockets%20were%20abandoned%2C%20but%20in%20some%2C%20the%20Sikhs%20had%20stayed%20behind%20but%20were%20unable%20to%20go%20back%20to%20making%20their%20daily%20bread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20can%20extol%20on%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20professional%20diversity%20almost%20endlessly%2C%20digging%20into%20recesses%20of%20memory%2C%20but%20that%20is%20not%20the%20principal%20%E2%80%98story%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELifelong%20friendships%20grew.%20The%20%E2%80%98kaali%20kitab%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20slim%20People%E2%80%99s%20Union%20for%20Civil%20Liberties-People%E2%80%99s%20Union%20for%20Democratic%20Rights%20(PUCL-PUDR)%20booklet%2C%20%3Cem%3EWho%20Are%20The%20Guilty%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20with%20its%20black%20cover%2C%20emerged%20from%20this%20collective.%20Petitions%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20government.%20Affidavits%20were%20filed%20and%20submitted%20to%20the%20Misra%20Commission%20and%20other%20official%20enquiries.%20Conversations%20moved%20to%20houses%20of%20the%20unspoken%20%E2%80%98leaders%E2%80%99.%20On%20return%20journeys%20from%20distant%20colonies%2C%20refugee%20camps%20and%20shelters%2C%20volunteers%20often%20halted%20for%20a%20quick%20snack%20at%20the%20houses%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98elders%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20elders%2C%20there%20was%20one%20who%20was%20particularly%20friendly%20with%20the%20younger%20ones.%20Initially%20we%20addressed%20her%20by%20the%20nickname%3A%20Lolly.%20Only%20after%20a%20few%20days%20it%20got%20known%2C%20she%20was%20Lalita%20Ramdas%2C%20married%20to%20a%20senior%20naval%20officer%2C%20who%20as%20we%20know%20became%20the%20naval%20chief%20six%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENEM%2C%20as%20the%20never-registered%20body%20was%20called%2C%20became%20the%20fountainhead%20of%20relief%20and%20rehabilitation%20plans%20of%20the%20displaced%2C%20investigation%2C%20collating%20and%20submission%20of%20evidence.%20It%20adopted%20a%20pronounced%20anti-government%20stance%20and%20in%20time%2C%20political%20divergences%20became%20pronounced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20barely%20forty%20years%2C%20but%20no%20accusations%20were%20hurled.%20No%20slurs%20were%20heard%2C%20no%20accusations%20were%20made%20that%20Khalistanis%20were%20being%20promoted%20and%20that%20the%20activities%20were%20anti-national.%20Moral%20and%20indignation%20may%20not%20have%20been%20endorsed%20by%20the%20State%2C%20but%20there%20was%20space%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20why%20the%20passing%20of%20Admiral%20Ramdas%20serves%20a%20reminder%20to%20the%20gory%20months%20of%201984%2C%20besides%20it%20being%20the%2040th%20anniversary%20year%2C%20was%20because%20such%20responses%20are%20unthinkable%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India.%20The%20regime%20then%2C%20disagreed%20with%20accusations%20made%2C%20stonewalled%20demands%20for%20proper%20investigations%20and%20rejected%20calls%20for%20punishing%20the%20accused%2C%20but%20at%20no%20point%20did%20they%20disparage%20critics%20and%20delegitimise%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2F1984-sikh-pogrom-riot-community-division%5C%22%3E1984%2C%20the%20State%2C%20a%20Carnage%20and%20What%20the%20Trauma%20of%20a%20People%20Means%20to%20India%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20two%20decades%20later%20and%20thereafter%2C%20the%20pogrom%20in%20Gujarat%20in%202002%20began%20being%20justified%20in%20the%20name%20of%201984%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cif%20they%20could%20have%20gone%20away%20with%201984%2C%20we%20are%20entitled%20to%202002%2C%E2%80%9D%20goes%20the%20creepy%20contention%20even%20now.%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20retained%20those%20%E2%80%98tainted%E2%80%99%20by%20reports%20on%20the%20gore%20of%20November%201984%2C%20but%20did%20not%20scream%20that%20a%20foreign-backed%2C%20media-led%20cartel%20of%20%3Cem%3Eliberandus%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20out%20to%20destabilise%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%201984%20has%20a%20long%20list%20of%20events%20for%20which%20there%20are%20no%20pleasant%20memories.%20But%20that%20era%20had%20a%20certain%20characteristic%20whose%20disappearance%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20can%20be%20bemoaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20indeed%20a%20%E2%80%98different%E2%80%99%20country%20then.%20A%20serving%2C%20celebrated%20naval%20officer%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20and%20connected%20with%20an%20NGO%20too%2C%20was%20involved%20in%20what%20was%20essentially%20a%20humanistic%20intervention%20against%20the%20grain%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20thinking%20at%20that%20time%2C%20to%20assist%20victims%20of%20the%20anti-Sikh%20carnage%20after%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20assassination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20when%20impromptu%20meetings%20were%20held%20at%20the%20stopgap%20residential%20arrangement%20provided%20by%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20for%20the%20Ramdas%20family%20and%20the%20Admiral%20on%20return%20from%20office%2C%20excused%20himself%20to%20the%20adjacent%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20fingers%20were%20pointed%20at%20him%20by%20the%20government%20for%20providing%20space%20to%20discuss%20matters%20that%20were%20against%20ruling%20party%20policies%20%E2%80%93%20he%20was%20even%20made%20the%20chief%20within%20a%20few%20years!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20unthinkable%20now.%20The%20State%20is%20more%20paranoid%20and%20driven%20by%20an%20exclusivist%20ideology%20than%20it%20has%20ever%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20nation%20can%20avoid%20misfortune.%20Mostly%2C%20the%20trauma%20of%201984%20was%20self-created.%20But%20there%20was%20still%20space%20for%20people%20who%20disagreed%20and%20flagged%20dissenting%20views%20on%20every%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%201984%2C%20this%20year%20too%20is%20an%20election%20year.%20The%20verdict%20of%201984%20remains%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20one-sided%20ever%2C%20but%20it%20took%20less%20than%2024%20months%20for%20the%20regime%20to%20start%20unraveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20brute%20majority%20in%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Opposition%2C%20civil%20society%20and%20media%20had%20space%20and%20liberty%20to%20remain%20faithful%20to%20their%20credo.%20Will%20this%20be%20possible%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20role%20model%20for%20people%20who%20wish%20to%20stay%20imprisoned%20by%20their%20conscience%2C%20like%20him%2C%20Admiral%20Ramdas%2C%20after%20retirement%20spoke%20for%20disarmament%2C%20civil%20liberties%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20more%2C%20but%20above%20all%2C%20for%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20presence%20will%20be%20felt%20eternally%20by%20even%20those%20who%20only%20heard%20or%20read%20about%20his%20bravery%2C%20on%20the%20battlefield%20and%20outside%20it.%20This%20makes%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20loss%20not%20just%20personal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENilanjan%20Mukhopadhyay%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi-NCR.%20His%20latest%20book%20is%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%98The%20Demolition%2C%20The%20Verdict%20and%20The%20Temple%3A%20The%20Definitive%20Book%20on%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20Project%E2%80%99%2C%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98Sikhs%3A%20The%20Untold%20Agony%20of%201984%E2%80%99%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98Narendra%20Modi%3A%20The%20Man%2C%20The%20Times%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHis%20X%20handle%20is%20%40NilanjanUdwin%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710574221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15144956%2FGIsGrdcW0AAoSLg.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fremembering-admiral-ramdas-and-how-india-was-different-in-1984%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20role%20model%20for%20people%20who%20wish%20to%20stay%20imprisoned%20by%20their%20conscience%2C%20like%20him%2C%20Admiral%20Ramdas%2C%20after%20retirement%20spoke%20for%20disarmament%2C%20civil%20liberties%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20more%2C%20but%20above%20all%2C%20for%20humanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fremembering-admiral-ramdas-and-how-india-was-different-in-1984%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20Admiral%20Ramdas%20And%20How%20India%20Was%20Different%20In%201984%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15144956%2FGIsGrdcW0AAoSLg.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20passing%20of%20Admiral%20Laxminarayan%20Ramdas%20evokes%20memories%20from%201984%20of%20a%20different%20India.%20Paradoxically%2C%20the%20only%20part%20he%20played%20in%20the%20events%20which%20evoked%20my%20recollections%20was%20possibly%20a%20conscious%20decision%20to%20look%20past%20what%20his%20other%20half%20and%20her%20associates%20were%20engaged%20in.%20That%20was%20the%20era%20when%20those%20in%20the%20regime%20were%20more%20sure-footed%20and%20did%20not%20shout%20%E2%80%98treason%E2%80%99%20at%20every%20step%20to%20consolidate%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20exactly%20four%20decades%20ago%2C%20had%20dawned%20in%20India%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20Jarnail%20Singh%20Bhindranwale%20being%20openly%20revered%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Esant%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20saint%20by%20large%20sections%20in%20Punjab.%20Using%20this%20image%2C%20he%20had%20entered%20the%20Akal%20Takht%2C%20the%20highest%20temporal%20seat%20of%20the%20Sikhs%2C%20and%20fortified%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20priest%20of%20the%20Takht%20protested%20but%20was%20ignored%20and%20both%20the%20Shiromani%20Gurudwara%20Prabandhak%20Committee%20and%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20chose%20silence%20as%20the%20safest%20path.%20He%20had%20claimed%20earlier%20that%20the%20Sikhs%20never%20demanded%20a%20separate%20state%20of%20Khalistan%20but%20if%20the%20government%20granted%20them%20the%20wish%2C%20they%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20secede.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20posture%20became%20less%20nuanced%20after%20moving%20into%20the%20Akal%20Takht%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20for%20the%20government%20to%20make%20up%20its%20mind%20whether%20it%20wishes%20to%20remain%20with%20us%20or%20not%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bhindranwale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20doubt%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20lost%20her%20hold%20over%20the%20fundamentalists%20and%20the%20moderates%20had%20retreated%20far%20into%20the%20background.%20Eventually%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20made%20up%20her%20mind%20and%20began%20firming%20up%20plans%20for%20launching%20Operation%20Blue%20Star.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20it%20was%20the%20gruesome%20assassination%20of%20Romesh%20Chandra%2C%20the%20editor%20of%20the%20Hind%20Samachar%20group%20%E2%80%94%20his%20father%20Lala%20Jagat%20Narain%20was%20also%20murdered%20by%20Sikh%20terrorists%20%E2%80%94%20in%20May%201984%2C%20which%20forced%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20seize%20control%20of%20the%20Golden%20Temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamchandra%20Guha%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20After%20Gandhi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20Operation%20Blue%20Star%20%E2%80%9Cleft%20a%20collective%20wound%20in%20the%20psyche%20of%20the%20Sikhs%2C%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20suspicion%20of%20the%20government%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20shared%20grief%20erupted%20on%20October%2031%20in%20the%20action%20of%20Delhi%20Police%20constables%2C%20Beant%20Singh%20and%20Satwant%20Singh%20and%20the%20rest%20is%20well-known%2C%20including%20the%20gory%20carnage%20that%20followed%20which%20left%20thousands%20dead%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Kanpur%2C%20Bokaro%20and%20even%20distant%20cities%20like%20Indore%20and%20Coimbatore%2C%20which%20witnessed%20uncalled%20for%20violence%20against%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20retributive%20assassination%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20round%20of%20vengeful%20killings%20on%20a%20mass%20scale%2C%20first%20in%20the%20Indian%20capital%2C%20and%20later%20in%20other%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20was%20solely%20engrossed%20in%20managing%20the%20biggest%20funeral%20in%20several%20decades%2C%20this%20one%20made%20more%20poignant%20due%20to%20the%20circumstances%20that%20led%20to%20it.%20Delhi%20was%20burning%20much%20before%20her%20pyre%20was%20lit.%20Whichever%20direction%20one%20turned%20to%2C%20there%20was%20smoke%20billowing.%20All%20stories%20that%20arrived%20by%20word%20of%20mouth%20and%20courtesy%20brave%20young%20reporters%20of%20that%20time%2C%20spoke%20of%20dead%20bodies%20either%20in%20heaps%20or%20in%20scatters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20television%20screen%20of%20the%20only%20state%20channel%20available%20then%2C%20was%20fixated%20on%20the%20face%20of%20the%20deceased%20leader%20and%20on%20dignitaries%20who%20arrived%20to%20pay%20homage.%20Rioters%2C%20lynch%20brigades%2C%20and%20arsonists%20roamed%20those%20streets%20where%20the%20police%20should%20have%20been%20patrolling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterventions%20from%20the%20civil%20society%20usually%20take%20the%20courage%20of%20only%20a%20handful.%20Initially%2C%20just%20a%20small%20group%20assembled%20outside%20what%20was%20then%2C%20and%20still%20so%2C%20the%20little%20known%20Lajpat%20Bhawan%2C%20a%20property%20of%20the%20Servants%20of%20the%20People%20Society%2C%20established%20by%20Lala%20Lajpat%20Rai%20in%20his%20Lahore%20home%20in%201921%20and%20later%20shifted%20to%20Delhi%20after%20partition.%20This%20was%20in%20addition%20to%20%E2%80%98peace%E2%80%99%20(and%20patrolling)%20committees%20in%20middle-class%20colonies%20across%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20walked%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20smoke%20that%20initially%20appeared%20to%20be%20across%20the%20Ring%20Road%20and%20beyond%20the%20Moolchand%20Hospital.%20Later%2C%20the%20smoke%20took%20them%20towards%20Bhogal%20and%20on%20the%20way%20they%20came%20across%20a%20mob%20breathing%20fire%20and%20ranting%20against%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobs%20are%20notoriously%20also%20weak-kneed%20and%20run%20short%20at%20the%20slightest%20bit%20of%20challenge.%20What%20made%20this%20group%20conspicuous%2C%20doing%20little%20but%20walking%2C%20reasoning%20and%20imploring%20with%20folded%20hands%2C%20was%20that%20it%20also%20included%20a%20man%20in%20saffron.%20In%20the%20India%20of%20that%20time%2C%20robes%20of%20this%20colour%20did%20not%20herald%20a%20zealot%20donning%20it.%20Instead%20it%20was%20the%20colour%20of%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwami%20Agnivesh%2C%20was%20not%20a%20guru%2C%20but%20an%20interventionist%20disillusioned%20with%20politics%20and%20much%20before%20such%20phrases%20caught%20on%2C%20was%20mainly%20a%20champion%20of%20marginal%20causes%3A%20rescuing%20child%20labour%20being%20one%20of%20those.%20After%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%2C%20in%20the%20course%20of%20which%20the%20group%20successfully%20sent%20back%20several%20marauding%20gangs%20with%20little%20but%20their%20persuasion%2C%20they%20assembled%20at%20the%20starting%20point%2C%20but%20this%20time%20inside%20the%20premises%20of%20this%20very%20Gandhian%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fex-naval-chief-admiral-laxminarayan-ramdas-passes-away-at-95%5C%22%3EAdmiral%20Ramdas%2C%20Former%20Navy%20Chief%20Who%20Fought%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Rights%2C%20Passes%20Away%20at%2090%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20any%20formal%20call%20being%20taken%2C%20this%20became%20the%20daily%20grind%20and%20as%20the%20group%20swelled%2C%20they%20travelled%20to%20far-flung%20areas%20from%20where%20%E2%80%98bad%E2%80%99%20or%20even%20%E2%80%98worse%E2%80%99%20news%20emanated.%20They%20drove%20their%20own%20cars%2C%20packing%20into%20the%20Fiats%2C%20Ambassadors%2C%20Standards%20and%20the%20odd%20Marutis.%20They%20went%20to%20distant%20localities%20and%20when%20a%20day%20or%20two%20later%2C%20they%20returned%20in%20the%20evening%20after%20seeing%20the%20grotesque%20scenes%20in%20Trilokpuri%2C%20all%20of%20them%20knew%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20shift%20gears.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpontaneity%20was%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20effort%20and%20soon%20hundreds%20were%20assembling%20every%20morning%20at%20Lajpat%20Nagar.%20The%20Gandhian%20managers%20of%20the%20premises%2C%20threw%20open%20every%20large%20vacant%20hall%20or%20room%20to%20store%20items%20that%20could%20be%20distributed%20as%20relief%20%E2%80%93%20cereals%2C%20pulses%2C%20cooking%20oil%2C%20utensils.%20Others%20came%20with%20clothes%2C%20warm%2C%20just%20enough%20to%20shield%20modesty%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20turbans%20that%20had%20been%20pulled%20and%20set%20to%20fire%20or%20trampled%20upon%2C%20by%20the%20murderous%20hordes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20boss%20giving%20directions.%20Everyone%20took%20their%20own%20decisions%20with%20minor%20consultations%20to%20avoid%20duplication.%20For%20many%20in%20the%20city%2C%20especially%20in%20Lajpat%20Nagar%20%E2%80%94%20originally%20allotted%20to%20refugee%20families%20from%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%94%20this%20was%20partition%20once%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20young%20aspiring%20journalist%2Fresearcher%2Fdo-not-know-what%2C%20I%20too%20got%20involved%2C%20drawn%20by%20a%20doyen%20of%20the%20civil%20society.%20A%20morning%20meeting%20where%20%E2%80%98work%E2%80%99%20was%20sought%20and%20%E2%80%98allotted%E2%80%99%20was%20followed%20by%20different%20groups%20following%20different%20tasks.%20Some%20fanned%20out%20to%20gurudwaras%20across%20the%20city%20where%20hundreds%20of%20displaced%20and%20targeted%20families%20took%20refuge%20from%20the%20killers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20handful%20focused%20on%20providing%20food%20and%20distributing%20clothes%20to%20provide%20relief%20from%20the%20onset%20of%20winter%2C%20while%20others%20gathered%20information.%20There%20was%20much%20of%20that%20needed%3A%20how%20many%20had%20not%20survived%20the%20onslaught%2C%20which%20localities%20were%20worst%20hit%20and%20above%20all%2C%20who%20were%20the%20marauders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20came%20up%20with%20a%20name%20that%20stuck%3A%20Nagrik%20Ekta%20Manch.%20The%20word%20was%20passed%20around.%20Obviously%20well-heeled%20ones%20too%20trooped%20in%2C%20and%20said%20that%20they%20were%20leaving%20behind%20a%20car%20with%20the%20driver%20waiting%20for%20directions%20and%20the%20tank%20topped%20up.%20Known%20faces%20abounded%2C%20a%20writer%2C%20an%20artist%2C%20a%20Doordarshan%20anchor%2C%20a%20big%20industrialist%2C%20university%20professors%2C%20environmentalists%2C%20a%20retired%20army%20general%20and%20serving%20government%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20a%20noted%20historian%20of%20today%2C%20then%20an%20aspiring%20one%2C%20I%20led%20a%20team%20every%20day%20to%20a%20resettlement%20colony%20on%20the%20western%20fringe%20of%20the%20metropolis%20%E2%80%93%20some%20pockets%20were%20abandoned%2C%20but%20in%20some%2C%20the%20Sikhs%20had%20stayed%20behind%20but%20were%20unable%20to%20go%20back%20to%20making%20their%20daily%20bread.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20can%20extol%20on%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20professional%20diversity%20almost%20endlessly%2C%20digging%20into%20recesses%20of%20memory%2C%20but%20that%20is%20not%20the%20principal%20%E2%80%98story%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELifelong%20friendships%20grew.%20The%20%E2%80%98kaali%20kitab%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20the%20slim%20People%E2%80%99s%20Union%20for%20Civil%20Liberties-People%E2%80%99s%20Union%20for%20Democratic%20Rights%20(PUCL-PUDR)%20booklet%2C%20%3Cem%3EWho%20Are%20The%20Guilty%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20with%20its%20black%20cover%2C%20emerged%20from%20this%20collective.%20Petitions%20were%20submitted%20to%20the%20government.%20Affidavits%20were%20filed%20and%20submitted%20to%20the%20Misra%20Commission%20and%20other%20official%20enquiries.%20Conversations%20moved%20to%20houses%20of%20the%20unspoken%20%E2%80%98leaders%E2%80%99.%20On%20return%20journeys%20from%20distant%20colonies%2C%20refugee%20camps%20and%20shelters%2C%20volunteers%20often%20halted%20for%20a%20quick%20snack%20at%20the%20houses%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98elders%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20elders%2C%20there%20was%20one%20who%20was%20particularly%20friendly%20with%20the%20younger%20ones.%20Initially%20we%20addressed%20her%20by%20the%20nickname%3A%20Lolly.%20Only%20after%20a%20few%20days%20it%20got%20known%2C%20she%20was%20Lalita%20Ramdas%2C%20married%20to%20a%20senior%20naval%20officer%2C%20who%20as%20we%20know%20became%20the%20naval%20chief%20six%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENEM%2C%20as%20the%20never-registered%20body%20was%20called%2C%20became%20the%20fountainhead%20of%20relief%20and%20rehabilitation%20plans%20of%20the%20displaced%2C%20investigation%2C%20collating%20and%20submission%20of%20evidence.%20It%20adopted%20a%20pronounced%20anti-government%20stance%20and%20in%20time%2C%20political%20divergences%20became%20pronounced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20barely%20forty%20years%2C%20but%20no%20accusations%20were%20hurled.%20No%20slurs%20were%20heard%2C%20no%20accusations%20were%20made%20that%20Khalistanis%20were%20being%20promoted%20and%20that%20the%20activities%20were%20anti-national.%20Moral%20and%20indignation%20may%20not%20have%20been%20endorsed%20by%20the%20State%2C%20but%20there%20was%20space%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20why%20the%20passing%20of%20Admiral%20Ramdas%20serves%20a%20reminder%20to%20the%20gory%20months%20of%201984%2C%20besides%20it%20being%20the%2040th%20anniversary%20year%2C%20was%20because%20such%20responses%20are%20unthinkable%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India.%20The%20regime%20then%2C%20disagreed%20with%20accusations%20made%2C%20stonewalled%20demands%20for%20proper%20investigations%20and%20rejected%20calls%20for%20punishing%20the%20accused%2C%20but%20at%20no%20point%20did%20they%20disparage%20critics%20and%20delegitimise%20criticism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2F1984-sikh-pogrom-riot-community-division%5C%22%3E1984%2C%20the%20State%2C%20a%20Carnage%20and%20What%20the%20Trauma%20of%20a%20People%20Means%20to%20India%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20two%20decades%20later%20and%20thereafter%2C%20the%20pogrom%20in%20Gujarat%20in%202002%20began%20being%20justified%20in%20the%20name%20of%201984%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cif%20they%20could%20have%20gone%20away%20with%201984%2C%20we%20are%20entitled%20to%202002%2C%E2%80%9D%20goes%20the%20creepy%20contention%20even%20now.%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20retained%20those%20%E2%80%98tainted%E2%80%99%20by%20reports%20on%20the%20gore%20of%20November%201984%2C%20but%20did%20not%20scream%20that%20a%20foreign-backed%2C%20media-led%20cartel%20of%20%3Cem%3Eliberandus%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20out%20to%20destabilise%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%201984%20has%20a%20long%20list%20of%20events%20for%20which%20there%20are%20no%20pleasant%20memories.%20But%20that%20era%20had%20a%20certain%20characteristic%20whose%20disappearance%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20can%20be%20bemoaned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20indeed%20a%20%E2%80%98different%E2%80%99%20country%20then.%20A%20serving%2C%20celebrated%20naval%20officer%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20and%20connected%20with%20an%20NGO%20too%2C%20was%20involved%20in%20what%20was%20essentially%20a%20humanistic%20intervention%20against%20the%20grain%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20thinking%20at%20that%20time%2C%20to%20assist%20victims%20of%20the%20anti-Sikh%20carnage%20after%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20assassination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20when%20impromptu%20meetings%20were%20held%20at%20the%20stopgap%20residential%20arrangement%20provided%20by%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20for%20the%20Ramdas%20family%20and%20the%20Admiral%20on%20return%20from%20office%2C%20excused%20himself%20to%20the%20adjacent%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20fingers%20were%20pointed%20at%20him%20by%20the%20government%20for%20providing%20space%20to%20discuss%20matters%20that%20were%20against%20ruling%20party%20policies%20%E2%80%93%20he%20was%20even%20made%20the%20chief%20within%20a%20few%20years!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20unthinkable%20now.%20The%20State%20is%20more%20paranoid%20and%20driven%20by%20an%20exclusivist%20ideology%20than%20it%20has%20ever%20been.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20nation%20can%20avoid%20misfortune.%20Mostly%2C%20the%20trauma%20of%201984%20was%20self-created.%20But%20there%20was%20still%20space%20for%20people%20who%20disagreed%20and%20flagged%20dissenting%20views%20on%20every%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%201984%2C%20this%20year%20too%20is%20an%20election%20year.%20The%20verdict%20of%201984%20remains%20India%E2%80%99s%20most%20one-sided%20ever%2C%20but%20it%20took%20less%20than%2024%20months%20for%20the%20regime%20to%20start%20unraveling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20brute%20majority%20in%20Parliament%2C%20the%20Opposition%2C%20civil%20society%20and%20media%20had%20space%20and%20liberty%20to%20remain%20faithful%20to%20their%20credo.%20Will%20this%20be%20possible%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20role%20model%20for%20people%20who%20wish%20to%20stay%20imprisoned%20by%20their%20conscience%2C%20like%20him%2C%20Admiral%20Ramdas%2C%20after%20retirement%20spoke%20for%20disarmament%2C%20civil%20liberties%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20more%2C%20but%20above%20all%2C%20for%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20presence%20will%20be%20felt%20eternally%20by%20even%20those%20who%20only%20heard%20or%20read%20about%20his%20bravery%2C%20on%20the%20battlefield%20and%20outside%20it.%20This%20makes%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20loss%20not%20just%20personal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENilanjan%20Mukhopadhyay%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi-NCR.%20His%20latest%20book%20is%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%98The%20Demolition%2C%20The%20Verdict%20and%20The%20Temple%3A%20The%20Definitive%20Book%20on%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20Project%E2%80%99%2C%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98Sikhs%3A%20The%20Untold%20Agony%20of%201984%E2%80%99%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98Narendra%20Modi%3A%20The%20Man%2C%20The%20Times%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHis%20X%20handle%20is%20%40NilanjanUdwin%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710574221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15144956%2FGIsGrdcW0AAoSLg.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fopinion%2Fremembering-admiral-ramdas-and-how-india-was-different-in-1984%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20role%20model%20for%20people%20who%20wish%20to%20stay%20imprisoned%20by%20their%20conscience%2C%20like%20him%2C%20Admiral%20Ramdas%2C%20after%20retirement%20spoke%20for%20disarmament%2C%20civil%20liberties%2C%20equality%2C%20and%20more%2C%20but%20above%20all%2C%20for%20humanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fopinion%2Fremembering-admiral-ramdas-and-how-india-was-different-in-1984%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boeing%20plane%20found%20with%20missing%20panel%20on%20landing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710573900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F70x70%2Fskynews-boeing-boeing-737-800_6491831.jpg%3F20240316080954%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Funited-airlines-flight-from-san-francisco-to-oregon-missing-boeing-plane-panel-on-landing-13095716%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20air%20safety%20officials%20are%20investigating%20a%20Boeing%20737-800%20plane%20th