0which%20are%20not%20accounted%20for%2C%20are%20actually%20about%204.3%20percentage%20points%20out%20of%20the%20estimated%207.6%25%20growth%20for%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20served%20as%20the%20chief%20economic%20adviser%20from%20October%202014%20to%20June%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20he%20also%20flagged%20that%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20(FDI)%20had%20declined%20very%20sharply%20in%20the%20last%20two%20or%20three%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20India%E2%80%99s%20FDI%20coming%20down%2C%20but%20also%20India%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20global%20FDI%20going%20to%20emerging%20markets%20has%20also%20come%20down.%20So%20the%20question%20is%2C%20if%20India%20has%20become%20such%20an%20attractive%20place%20to%20invest%2C%20why%20isn%E2%80%99t%20there%20more%20FDI%3F%20Corporate%20investment%20is%20also%20well%20below%202016%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-gdp-slow-consumption-savings-workforce-thriving-or-surviving%5C%22%3EWith%20a%20Rising%20GDP%2C%20but%20Slow%20Consumption%20and%20Low%20Savings%2C%20Is%20India%E2%80%99s%20Workforce%20Thriving%20or%20Surviving%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20economy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fgdp-grew-by-8-4-in-october-december-quarter-of-fy24-govt-data%5C%22%3Egrew%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20better-than-expected%208.4%25%20in%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20of%20fiscal%20year%202024%20%E2%80%93%20the%20fastest%20pace%20in%20one-and-half%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NSO%20has%20also%20revised%20GDP%20estimates%20for%20the%20first%20and%20second%20quarters%20of%20this%20fiscal%20to%208.2%25%20and%208.1%25%20from%207.8%25%20and%207.6%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Subramanian%20expressed%20concerns%20over%20the%20latest%20GDP%20numbers%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20forme