ihood%20for%20underprivileged%20women.%20It%20is%20called%20the%20Save%20Prithvi%20Foundation%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoonam%20is%20now%20a%20master%20trainer%20at%20Khadi%20India%2C%20National%20Cooperative%20Union%20of%20India%2C%20and%20has%20conducted%20training%20programmes%20with%20many%20government%20organisations%20like%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendras%20in%20Jammu%2C%20the%20rural%20development%20programme%20and%20more.%20She%20has%20trained%20over%203%2C000%20women%20and%20showed%20them%20a%20way%20to%20become%20self-reliant%2C%20while%20helping%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20collects%20floral%20waste%20from%20over%2015%20temples%20in%20Delhi-NCR%20today%20and%20gets%20almost%20100%20kg%20of%20waste%20every%20three%20days.%20Besides%20dhoop%2C%20which%20is%20her%20bestseller%2C%20she%20makes%20idols%20and%20air%20fresheners.%20Her%20products%20range%20from%20Rs%2050-350%2C%20earning%20her%20a%20monthly%20income%20of%20Rs%202%20lakh.%20Her%20dhoop%20stand%20and%20packaging%20too%2C%20is%20made%20from%20waste.%20She%20employs%205%20women%20at%20her%20unit%2C%20who%20she%20calls%20the%20%E2%80%98flower%20recyclers%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Poonam%2C%20this%20business%20helped%20her%20build%20her%20identity%20and%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20environment%20and%20lives%20of%20countless%20women.%20Her%20dream%20is%20to%20make%20India%20a%20country%20where%20not%20even%20one%20religious%20place%20throws%20flowers%20in%20the%20garbage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20all%20women%20like%20her%2C%20looking%20to%20fulfil%20their%20dream%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20get%20one%20opportunity%20in%20life%20to%20carve%20a%20path%20for%20ourselves.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20miss%20it.%20Live%20for%20yourself%20and%20do%20what%20makes%20you%20happy.%20The%20first%20step%20is%20always%20difficult%2C%20but%20once%20you%E2%80%99ve%20taken%20it%2C%20there%20is%20no%20looking%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5C